+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DiydiRGXuaickuwVvxtrer","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Phase 4: Delayed and Scheduled Tasks\n     2→\n     3→Add the ability to defer tasks so they only become available for processing after a specified time.\n     4→\n     5→## Requirements\n     6→\n     7→- A task can be given a delay (in milliseconds) or a specific future time at which it becomes available.\n     8→- Delayed tasks are added to the queue immediately but are not returned when retrieving until their availability time has passed.\n     9→- Non-delayed tasks are always preferred over delayed tasks that are not yet available.\n    10→- When multiple delayed tasks become available simultaneously, they should be ordered by availability time, then priority, then FIFO.\n    11→- The task object should indicate when it becomes available.\n    12→- Delays work correctly with named queues.\n    13→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Sd3qWQPH9SWasj5wfUX62o","session_id":"9ffff21e-55a2-42c3-9982-0a1b8673eedf","uuid":"dacf172f-a2c4-49f7-8b0f-088bafbeac47"}
