ogress & Cancellation)\n  - Phase 10: 7 tests (Recurring Tasks/Cron)\n  - Phase 11: 7 tests (Middleware Pipeline)\n  - Phase 12: 8 tests (Graceful Shutdown)\n\n### 12 Phase Requirements (Complete Details)\n\n#### Phase 1: Basic FIFO Queue\n- Accept payload when task added, return task object\n- Each task has: unique ID (UUID), status, creation timestamp\n- New tasks start in \"pending\" state\n- Retrieving returns oldest pending task, transitions to \"processing\"\n- Returns `null` if no tasks available\n- Ability to check number of waiting tasks\n\n#### Phase 2: Named Queues\n- Tasks added to specific named queue (default queue if not specified)\n- Each queue operates independently\n- Retrieval pulls from specified queue only\n- Queue creation implicit on first task add\n- Way to list all existing queue names\n- Non-existent/empty queue returns `null`\n- Backward-compatible with Phase 1\n\n#### Phase 3: Priority\n- Priority levels 1 (highest) to 10 (lowest), default 5\n- Higher-priority tasks returned first on retrieval\n- Same priority: FIFO order\n- Invalid priorities cause error\n- Priority per-queue\n- Task object exposes priority level\n\n#### Phase 4: Delayed and Scheduled Tasks\n- Tasks can have delay (milliseconds) or specific future time\n- Delayed tasks stored immediately but not returned until available\n- Non-delayed tasks preferred over unavailable delayed tasks\n- Multiple delayed tasks: ordered by availability time, then priority, then FIFO\n- Task object shows availability time\n- Works with named queues\n\n#### Phase 5: Retry with Backoff\n- Way to mark processing task as completed or failed\n- Failed tasks with retries re-added with delay\n- Exponential backoff: `baseDelay * 2^(attempt - 1)` (e.g., 1s, 2s, 4s, ...)\n- Default max retries: 3 (configurable per task)\n- Default base delay: 1000ms (configurable per task)\n- Task tracks attempt count\n- Retried tasks keep original queue and priority\n- All retries exhausted: task remains failed\n\n#### Phase 6: Dead Letter Queue\n- Failed tasks with no retries moved to DLQ for original queue\n- Way to view all dead-lettered tasks for queue\n- Dead-lettered tasks retain error info and failure count\n- Ability to move dead-lettered task back for fresh retries\n- Way to clear all dead-lettered tasks for queue\n- Each queue has independent DLQ\n\n#### Phase 7: Task Dependencies\n- Tasks can declare dependencies on other task IDs\n- Task with unresolved dependencies blocked, not returned\n- When dependency completes, check unblocked tasks\n- Circular dependencies detected and rejected at creation\n- Depending on non-existent task causes error\n- Failed dependency doesn't fail dependents (remain blocked)\n- Way to inspect task's dependency status\n\n#### Phase 8: Concurrency Control\n- Per-queue maximum concurrency setting\n- Limits tasks in processing state simultaneously\n- Concurrency limit reached: returns `null` even if pending tasks exist\n- Completing/failing task frees concurrency slot\n- Default: no limit (unlimited)\n- Way to set/query concurrency limit and active count\n- Highest-priority available task chosen subject to concurrency limit\n\n#### Phase 9: Progress Tracking and Cancellation\n- Processing task can report progress (0-100%) with optional message\n- Way to query task's current progress\n- Listeners can subscribe to progress updates, receive notifications\n- Subscriptions cancellable (unsubscribe)\n- Pending/processing tasks can be cancelled\n- Cancelled pending tasks removed from queue\n- Cancelled processing tasks have status updated\n- Cancelled tasks never retried\n\n#### Phase 10: Recurring Tasks\n- Schedule associates cron expression with queue and task template\n- Supported cron expressions:\n  - `*/N * * * *` - every N minutes\n  - `0 * * * *` - every hour on the hour\n  - `0 0 * * *` - every day at midnight\n- Way to create, remove, list active schedules\n- Manual \"tick\"/\"check\" mechanism evaluates schedules, enqueues due tasks\n- Recurring tasks become regular tasks once enqueued\n- Removing schedule stops future occurrences\n\n#### Phase 11: Middleware Pipeline\n- Middleware functions registered per queue\n- Task passes through all registered middleware in order\n- Each middleware receives task and \"next\" function\n- Not calling \"next\" skips remaining processing\n- Middleware can modify task (metadata, payload transformation)\n- Middleware error: task marked failed\n- Processing handler registered per queue, invoked after middleware\n- Each queue has independent middleware stack\n\n#### Phase 12: Graceful Shutdown\n- Shutdown signals system to stop accepting new tasks\n- Adding tasks after shutdown produces error\n- Shutdown waits for processing tasks up to configurable timeout\n- Unfinished tasks after timeout: force-cancelled\n- Callbacks can be registered for shutdown process\n- Shutdown produces summary: completed, force-cancelled, duration\n- Multiple shutdown calls safe, return same result\n- No processing tasks: shutdown completes immediately\n\n### Current Source Code Status\n**The `/workspace/src/` directory is empty** (only contains `.gitkeep` marker). This is the greenfield starting state where all implementation should be built.\n\n### Entry Point\n- Main API must be exported from `/workspace/src/index.ts`\n- All implementation should live under `/workspace/src/`\n- No external runtime dependencies allowed (dev dependencies pre-installed)\n\n### Validation Requirements\n```bash\nnpm run build   # TypeScript must compile successfully\nnpm run lint    # No lint errors\nnpm test        # All 90 tests must pass (10 tests × 9 phases = 90 total)\n```\n\nThis is a comprehensive marathon benchmark where later phases force rethinking early decisions. The design must be extensible to accommodate features like priorities, delays, dependencies, and middleware without major refactoring."}],"totalDurationMs":40084,"totalTokens":21653,"totalToolUseCount":23,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_cr